Help for RMATCH:

RMATCH shows all users whose
nick!user@host gecos
matches the given POSIX extended
regular expression.

Prefix your pattern with !i: to do a
case insensitive match.

Syntax: RMATCH <[!i:]regexp>

Example:
    /msg &nick& RMATCH !i:^m(oo|00)cow
    /msg &nick& RMATCH ^[a-z]+!~?[a-z]+@
    /msg &nick& RMATCH ^[^ ]* [^ ]*$
